To determine the day 1740 years ago from 2012-4-10, we need to calculate the difference in years and then use that to determine the day of the week.

Here's the Python code to calculate the day of the week 1740 years ago:
```python
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

# Define the input date
input_date = datetime(2012, 4, 10)

# Calculate the number of years ago
years_ago = 1740

# Subtract the years from the input date
date_1740_years_ago = input_date - timedelta(days=years_ago*365)

# Determine the day of the week 1740 years ago
day_of_week_1740_years_ago = date_1740_years_ago.strftime('A')

# Print the day of the week
print("The day 1740 years ago was:", day_of_week_1740_years_ago)
```
When you run this code, it will output the day of the week that was 1740 years ago from 2012-4-10.
